Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @long green pepper{1} into strips. Halve and peel
@yellow onion{1}; thinly slice one half (whole onion for 4 servings).

Place @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until
just softened, ~{10-15%seconds}. Stir in @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} and a pinch
of @salt{pinch}.

> Be sure to measure the garlic powder; we sent more.

Heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add green pepper, sliced onion, and a pinch of salt and
@pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and lightly charred,
~{5-7%minutes}.

> Tip: Add splashes of water as needed to prevent veggies from burning.

Transfer to a #plate{}.

Meanwhile, remove @Italian pork sausage{9%ounce} from casing; discard casing.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add sausage
and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through,
~{4-6%minutes}.

> If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

Stir @tomato paste{1.5%ounce}, @water{1/2%cup}, and half the
@Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon} into pan with sausage.

> For 4 servings, stir in 1 cup water and all the Italian Seasoning.

Cook, stirring, until sauce is bubbling, ~{1-2%minutes}. Taste and season with
salt and pepper.

Halve @demi-baguette{2} lengthwise, stopping before you get all the way through.
Spread cut sides with garlic butter. Place cut sides up on a #baking sheet{}.

> Tip: Line sheet with foil first for easier cleanup.

Toast on middle rack until bread is golden, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Carefully spoon sausage mixture onto bottom halves; top with veggies and
@mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}.

> Tip: The sandwiches are supposed to be messy—don't be afraid to pile them high!

Return to middle rack until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

== Side Salad ==

Place @mixed greens{2%ounce} in a large #bowl{}; toss with @Italian dressing{1.5%ounce}. 
Season with salt and pepper.

Close heroes, pressing down to secure. Divide between plates. Serve with salad
on the side.